---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import USBadge from '../components/USBadge.astro';
import TipTiers from '../components/TipTiers.astro';
import { tipping, usBaseline, tippingChecked } from '../data/tipping.js';

// Everything on this page reads from tipping.js live. Nothing is re-typed here,
// so correcting a row in the data corrects the bands, the callouts and the list
// on the next build.
const rows = tipping;

const TIERS = ['Not customary', 'Round up only', 'Small optional', 'Modest customary', 'Expected / standard'];
const tierCount = t => rows.filter(r => r.tier === t).length;

// The clusters worth calling out by name, all derived rather than listed by hand.
const noTip = rows.filter(r => r.tierRank === 0);
const usLevel = rows.filter(r => r.tierRank === 4);
const cashEssential = rows.filter(r => /essential/i.test(r.cashOrCard));
// Places where a service charge is normal but staff still expect something on
// top, the combination most likely to catch a US traveler out.
const chargePlusTip = rows.filter(r => r.serviceCharge !== 'rarely' && /additional tip expected/i.test(r.tipOnTop));

const regionsPresent = [...new Set(rows.map(r => r.region))].sort();
const chargeLevels = ['always', 'often', 'rarely'];
const chargeLabel = { always: 'Usually on the bill', often: 'Often on the bill', rarely: 'Rarely on the bill' };

function niceDate(iso) {
  if (!iso) return '';
  const d = new Date(iso + 'T00:00:00');
  if (isNaN(d.getTime())) return iso;
  return d.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long' });
}
const checkedLabel = niceDate(tippingChecked);

const title = 'Tipping by country, compared to what US travelers do at home | True Trip Costs';
const description = 'How tipping works in ' + rows.length + ' countries, measured against the US habit of 15 to 20 percent. Custom, not law: what to leave, whether a service charge is already on the bill, and whether to use cash. Checked ' + checkedLabel + '.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="wrap tipage">
    <p class="ctx"><USBadge /> <span class="stamp">Checked {checkedLabel}</span></p>
    <h1>Tipping, measured against what you do at home</h1>

    <p class="tipage-lede">
      The hard part is not what to tip in any one country. It is that your American instincts are wrong in
      most of the world, and you cannot tell by how much. So this page uses the habit you already have,
      {usBaseline.restaurant} at a US restaurant, as the yardstick for all {rows.length} countries.
      Only {usLevel.length} tip anywhere near US levels. {noTip.length} expect nothing at all.
    </p>

    <div class="tipage-honest">
      <p class="tipage-honest-h">This is custom, not law</p>
      <p>
        Tipping norms are social habits, not published rules, and they vary by region, venue and season.
        Individual places set their own policies, and a busy tourist strip often behaves differently from a
        neighborhood spot an hour away. That makes this page a different kind of claim from our visa-fee and
        tourist-tax pages, where the figures come from government sources. Treat what follows as well-researched
        guidance to travel with, not as rules. Sourcing quality varies by country and every entry shows how
        firm it is.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="tipage-bands" aria-label="Tipping tiers compared to the US">
      <TipTiers rows={rows} baseline={usBaseline} tiers={TIERS} id="tiers" />
    </section>

    <section class="tipage-calls" aria-label="What matters most">
      <div class="tc">
        <p class="tc-h">Do not tip in these {noTip.length}</p>
        <p class="tc-b">
          The single most useful thing on this page. In {noTip.map(r => r.country).join(', ')}, leaving money
          is not the norm, and in Japan it may be politely refused. Paying the exact amount is correct and
          not rude.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tc">
        <p class="tc-h">A service charge does not always reach the staff</p>
        <p class="tc-b">
          This one inverts the US assumption. In Taiwan the printed service charge is treated by law as
          general restaurant revenue rather than a gratuity. In Egypt, Argentina, Georgia and Vietnam it
          commonly does not reach the worker either. So "there is a service charge" does not reliably mean
          "staff are taken care of", and a small amount handed over in cash often lands where the printed
          charge does not.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tc">
        <p class="tc-h">Bring cash in these {cashEssential.length}</p>
        <p class="tc-b">
          In {cashEssential.map(r => r.country).join(', ')} a tip realistically has to be cash. In Argentina
          card terminals have no tip line at all, so anything you intend for the server has to come out of
          your pocket.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tc">
        <p class="tc-h">The money-side summary</p>
        <p class="tc-b">
          For budgeting rather than etiquette: across Europe and Japan, set aside almost nothing extra for
          tips, the price you see is close to the price you pay. Across North America and the Caribbean,
          budget a real 10 to 20 percent line item on top of every meal, and carry small bills, because that
          is where tipping genuinely moves your daily spend.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tipage-detail" aria-labelledby="every-country">
      <h2 id="every-country">Every country, with the one thing to remember</h2>
      <p class="tipage-sub">
        Filter to what you need. Each entry shows whether a service charge is usually on the bill, whether to
        tip in cash or card, and how firm our sourcing is.
      </p>

      <div class="tf" id="tip-filters">
        <div class="tf-group">
          <p class="tf-lab">Tier <span class="tf-count" id="tf-count">{rows.length} of {rows.length} shown</span></p>
          <div class="tf-btns" role="group" aria-label="Filter by tipping tier">
            <button type="button" class="tf-chip is-active" data-tier-btn="__all" aria-pressed="true">All</button>
            {TIERS.map(t => (
              <button type="button" class="tf-chip" data-tier-btn={t} aria-pressed="false">{t} <span class="tf-n">{tierCount(t)}</span></button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tf-group">
          <p class="tf-lab">Service charge</p>
          <div class="tf-btns" role="group" aria-label="Filter by service charge">
            <button type="button" class="tf-chip is-active" data-charge-btn="__all" aria-pressed="true">All</button>
            {chargeLevels.map(c => (
              <button type="button" class="tf-chip" data-charge-btn={c} aria-pressed="false">{chargeLabel[c]}</button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tf-group">
          <p class="tf-lab">Region</p>
          <div class="tf-btns" role="group" aria-label="Filter by region">
            <button type="button" class="tf-chip is-active" data-region-btn="__all" aria-pressed="true">All</button>
            {regionsPresent.map(r => (
              <button type="button" class="tf-chip" data-region-btn={r} aria-pressed="false">{r}</button>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <ol class="tl" id="tip-list">
        {rows.map(r => (
          <li
            class:list={["tl-row", 'is-' + r.confidence]}
            data-tier={r.tier}
            data-charge={r.serviceCharge}
            data-region={r.region}
          >
            <div class="tl-top">
              <span class="tl-country">
                {r.hasGuide ? <a href={`/${r.slug}`}>{r.country}</a> : <span>{r.country}</span>}
              </span>
              <span class="tl-tier">{r.tier}</span>
              <span class={`tl-conf is-${r.confidence}`}>{r.confidence === 'low' ? 'thin sourcing' : r.confidence === 'medium' ? 'less certain' : 'firmer'}</span>
            </div>

            <p class="tl-remember">{r.remember}</p>

            <dl class="tl-facts">
              <div><dt>Restaurant</dt><dd>{r.restaurant}</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Service charge</dt><dd>{chargeLabel[r.serviceCharge]}</dd></div>
              <div><dt>On top of it</dt><dd>{r.tipOnTop}</dd></div>
              <div><dt>Cash or card</dt><dd>{r.cashOrCard}</dd></div>
            </dl>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ol>

      <p class="tl-empty" id="tl-empty" hidden>Nothing matches those filters together. Reset one of them to see countries again.</p>
    </section>

    <p class="tipage-foot">
      Checked {checkedLabel} by the True Trip Costs desk. Tipping norms move faster than most travel facts:
      card terminals keep nudging suggested percentages upward, Turkey banned mandatory service charges in
      2026, and a 2025 Indian court ruling confirmed service charges there are voluntary. We re-check this
      page as norms shift, and where sources disagreed we lowered the confidence rather than picking a
      number that looked tidy.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <style>
    .tipage{max-width:900px}
    .tipage h1{margin-bottom:12px}
    .tipage-lede{font-size:17.5px;color:#3B4A46;line-height:1.55;max-width:680px;margin:0 0 20px}

    .tipage-honest{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:3px solid var(--teal);border-radius:12px;padding:14px 18px;margin:0 0 26px;max-width:720px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
    .tipage-honest-h{font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--teal-deep);margin:0 0 6px}
    .tipage-honest p{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55;margin:0}

    .tipage-bands{margin:0 0 34px}

    .tipage-calls{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:12px;margin:0 0 40px}
    .tc{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:14px 16px}
    .tc-h{font-size:14.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin:0 0 6px}
    .tc-b{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55;margin:0}

    .tipage-detail h2{font-family:var(--serif);font-weight:500;font-size:clamp(22px,3.4vw,30px);letter-spacing:-.01em;margin:0 0 8px}
    .tipage-sub{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 18px;max-width:640px}

    .tf{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;margin:0 0 20px}
    .tf-lab{font-size:12.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin:0 0 7px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap}
    .tf-count{font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);font-size:12px}
    .tf-btns{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:7px}
    .tf-chip{font:inherit;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:999px;padding:6px 12px;cursor:pointer;transition:background .16s ease,border-color .16s ease,color .16s ease}
    .tf-chip:hover{border-color:var(--amber);color:var(--amber)}
    .tf-chip.is-active{background:var(--amber);border-color:var(--amber);color:#fff}
    .tf-n{opacity:.75;font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums}

    .tl{list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px}
    .tl-row{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:13px 15px}
    .tl-row.is-hidden{display:none}
    /* Always-on confidence: a left edge that reads solid, soft, or provisional. */
    .tl-row.is-high{border-left:3px solid rgba(10,86,68,.75)}
    .tl-row.is-medium{border-left:3px solid rgba(10,86,68,.34)}
    .tl-row.is-low{border-left:3px dashed rgba(14,122,95,.6)}

    .tl-top{display:flex;align-items:baseline;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:9px;margin:0 0 6px}
    .tl-country{font-size:15.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink)}
    .tl-country a{color:var(--ink);text-decoration:none}
    .tl-country a:hover{color:var(--teal-deep);text-decoration:underline}
    .tl-tier{font-size:11.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);background:var(--paper);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:999px;padding:2px 9px}
    .tl-conf{font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.02em}
    .tl-conf.is-high{color:#10502C}
    .tl-conf.is-medium{color:#7A3D08}
    .tl-conf.is-low{color:var(--muted);font-style:italic}

    /* The practical takeaway stays visible at every width, never behind a hover. */
    .tl-remember{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.5;margin:0 0 9px;max-width:660px}

    .tl-facts{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(160px,1fr));gap:8px 14px;margin:0}
    .tl-facts div{min-width:0}
    .tl-facts dt{font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin:0 0 1px}
    .tl-facts dd{font-size:13px;color:var(--ink);margin:0;line-height:1.4}

    .tl-empty{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin:14px 0 0}
    .tipage-foot{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55;margin:34px 0 8px;max-width:700px}

    @media (max-width:560px){
      .tipage-lede{font-size:16.5px}
      .tipage-calls{grid-template-columns:1fr}
      .tl-remember{font-size:14px}
      .tl-facts{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:8px 10px}
      .tl-facts dd{font-size:12.5px}
    }
  </style>

  <script is:inline>
    (function () {
      var list = document.getElementById('tip-list');
      if (!list) return;
      var rows = Array.prototype.slice.call(list.querySelectorAll('.tl-row'));
      var countEl = document.getElementById('tf-count');
      var emptyEl = document.getElementById('tl-empty');
      var total = rows.length;

      var sel = { tier: '__all', charge: '__all', region: '__all' };

      function apply() {
        var shown = 0;
        rows.forEach(function (row) {
          var okTier = sel.tier === '__all' || row.getAttribute('data-tier') === sel.tier;
          var okCharge = sel.charge === '__all' || row.getAttribute('data-charge') === sel.charge;
          var okRegion = sel.region === '__all' || row.getAttribute('data-region') === sel.region;
          var hidden = !(okTier && okCharge && okRegion);
          row.classList.toggle('is-hidden', hidden);
          if (!hidden) shown++;
        });
        if (countEl) countEl.textContent = shown + ' of ' + total + ' shown';
        if (emptyEl) emptyEl.hidden = shown !== 0;
      }

      // Each filter group is single-select, so the three read as one sentence:
      // this tier, this service charge, this region.
      function wire(attr, key) {
        var btns = document.querySelectorAll('[' + attr + ']');
        btns.forEach(function (btn) {
          btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
            sel[key] = btn.getAttribute(attr);
            btns.forEach(function (x) {
              var on = x === btn;
              x.classList.toggle('is-active', on);
              x.setAttribute('aria-pressed', on ? 'true' : 'false');
            });
            apply();
          });
        });
      }

      wire('data-tier-btn', 'tier');
      wire('data-charge-btn', 'charge');
      wire('data-region-btn', 'region');
    })();
  </script>
</Base>
